t11FcRscnMIB.name: t11FcRscnMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module, published as RFC 4983.

t11FcRscnMIB.organization: For the initial versions, T11. For later versions, the IETF's IMSS Working Group.
t11FcRscnMIB.contactinfo: Claudio DeSanti Cisco Systems, Inc. 170 West Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA EMail: cds@cisco.com Keith McCloghrie Cisco Systems, Inc. 170 West Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA EMail: kzm@cisco.com
t11FcRscnMIB.description: The MIB module for the management of registrations by Nx_Ports to receive RSCNs (Registered State Change Notifications) on a Fibre Channel Fabric, as defined in FC-LS, and for the monitoring of RSCNs sent/received or rejected in a Fibre Channel Fabric. Copyright (C) The Internet Society (2007). This version of this MIB module is part of RFC 4983; see the RFC itself for full legal notices.

t11FcRscnRegTable.name: t11FcRscnRegTable
t11FcRscnRegTable.description: A table of Nx_Ports that have registered to receive RSCNs on all Fabrics configured on one or more Fibre Channel switches.

t11FcRscnRegEntry.name: t11FcRscnRegEntry
t11FcRscnRegEntry.description: An entry containing information about one Nx_Port that has registered with a particular switch (identified by values of fcmInstanceIndex and fcmSwitchIndex) for a particular Fabric (identified by a t11FcRscnFabricIndex value).

t11FcRscnFabricIndex.name: t11FcRscnFabricIndex
t11FcRscnFabricIndex.reference: ANSI INCITS 418-2006, Fibre Channel - Switch Fabric - 4 (FC-SW-4), December 2006.
t11FcRscnFabricIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a particular Fabric. In a Fabric conformant to FC-SW-4, multiple Virtual Fabrics can operate within one (or more) physical infrastructures. In such a case, this index value is used to uniquely identify a particular Fabric within a physical infrastructure. In a Fabric that has (or can have) only a single Fabric operating within the physical infrastructure, the value of this Fabric Index will always be 1.

t11FcRscnRegFcId.name: t11FcRscnRegFcId
t11FcRscnRegFcId.description: The Fibre Channel Address Identifier of the registering Nx_Port.

t11FcRscnRegType.name: t11FcRscnRegType
t11FcRscnRegType.reference: ANSI INCITS 433-2007, Fibre Channel - Link Services (FC-LS), July 2007, Table 40.
t11FcRscnRegType.description: This object indicates the type of registration desired by the registering Nx_Port, one bit per type: 'fromFabricController' -- RSCNs generated for events detected by the Fabric Controller. 'fromNxPorts' -- RSCNs generated for events detected by the affected Nx_Port.

t11FcRscnStatsTable.name: t11FcRscnStatsTable
t11FcRscnStatsTable.description: The RSCN-related statistics on all Fabrics configured on one or more Fibre Channel switches. Two levels of statistics are included: 1) counters at the message-type level, for: - the number of SCRs received/rejected, - the number of RSCNs sent/received/rejected, - the number of SW_RSCNs sent/received/rejected. 2) counters of sent/received RSCNs per 'Event Qualifier' value. Note that if and when several RSCN events are coalesced into a single RSCN message, then that message may be counted in more than one of these counters.

t11FcRscnStatsEntry.name: t11FcRscnStatsEntry
t11FcRscnStatsEntry.description: An entry containing statistics for a particular Fabric (identified by a t11FcRscnFabricIndex value) on a particular switch (identified by values of fcmInstanceIndex and fcmSwitchIndex).

t11FcRscnInScrs.name: t11FcRscnInScrs
t11FcRscnInScrs.description: The number of SCRs received from Nx_Ports by this switch on this Fabric. This counter has no discontinuities other than those that all Counter32s have when sysUpTime=0.

t11FcRscnInRscns.name: t11FcRscnInRscns
t11FcRscnInRscns.description: The number of RSCNs received from Nx_Ports by this switch on this Fabric. This counter has no discontinuities other than those that all Counter32s have when sysUpTime=0.

t11FcRscnOutRscns.name: t11FcRscnOutRscns
t11FcRscnOutRscns.description: The number of RSCNs transmitted to Nx_Ports by this switch on this Fabric. This counter has no discontinuities other than those that all Counter32s have when sysUpTime=0.

t11FcRscnInSwRscns.name: t11FcRscnInSwRscns
t11FcRscnInSwRscns.description: The number of SW_RSCNs received by this switch from other switches on this Fabric. This counter has no discontinuities other than those that all Counter32s have when sysUpTime=0.

t11FcRscnOutSwRscns.name: t11FcRscnOutSwRscns

t11FcRscnSwRscnRejects.name: t11FcRscnSwRscnRejects

t11FcRscnInUnspecifiedRscns.name: t11FcRscnInUnspecifiedRscns
t11FcRscnInUnspecifiedRscns.reference: ANSI INCITS 433-2007, Fibre Channel - Link Services (FC-LS), July 2007, Table 36.
t11FcRscnInUnspecifiedRscns.description: The number of Registered State Change Notifications (RSCNs) received by this switch on this Fabric which contained an RSCN Event Qualifier value of '0000'b meaning 'Event is not specified'. This counter has no discontinuities other than those that all Counter32s have when sysUpTime=0.

t11FcRscnOutUnspecifiedRscns.description: The number of Registered State Change Notifications (RSCNs) sent by this switch on this Fabric which contained an RSCN Event Qualifier value of '0000'b meaning 'Event is not specified'. This counter has no discontinuities other than those that all Counter32s have when sysUpTime=0.

t11FcRscnNotifyControlTable.name: t11FcRscnNotifyControlTable
t11FcRscnNotifyControlTable.description: A table of control information for notifications generated due to the rejection of an SCR or RSCN.

t11FcRscnNotifyControlEntry.name: t11FcRscnNotifyControlEntry
t11FcRscnNotifyControlEntry.description: Each entry contains notification control information concerning the rejection of RSCN/SCRs for a particular Fabric (identified by the value of t11FcRscnFabricIndex) by a particular switch (identified by values of fcmInstanceIndex and fcmSwitchIndex).

t11FcRscnIlsRejectNotifyEnable.name: t11FcRscnIlsRejectNotifyEnable
t11FcRscnIlsRejectNotifyEnable.description: This object specifies if a t11FcRscnIlsRejectReqNotify notification should be generated when this switch rejects an SW_RSCN on this Fabric. Values written to this object should be retained over agent reboots.

t11FcRscnElsRejectNotifyEnable.name: t11FcRscnElsRejectNotifyEnable
t11FcRscnElsRejectNotifyEnable.description: This object specifies if a t11FcRscnElsRejectReqNotify notification should be generated when this switch rejects an RSCN or SCR on this Fabric. Values written to this object should be retained over agent reboots.

t11FcRscnRejectedRequestString.name: t11FcRscnRejectedRequestString
t11FcRscnRejectedRequestString.reference: ANSI INCITS 433-2007, Fibre Channel - Link Services (FC-LS), July 2007, Tables 34 & 39. ANSI INCITS 418-2006, Fibre Channel - Switch Fabric - 4 (FC-SW-4), December 2006, Table 45.
t11FcRscnRejectedRequestString.description: The binary content of the RSCN, SCR, or SW_RSCN that was most recently rejected by this switch on this Fabric. The value is formatted as an octet string (in network byte order) as described in the relevant Fibre Channel standard, containing the payload (which is typically a list of affected ports and error codes) of the rejected RSCN or SCR as described in FC-LS, or the rejected SW_RSCN as described in FC-SW-4. This object contains the zero-length string if and when the RSCN/SCR/SW_RSCN payload is unavailable. When the length of this object is 255 octets, it contains the first 255 octets of the payload (in network byte order).

t11FcRscnRejectedRequestSource.name: t11FcRscnRejectedRequestSource
t11FcRscnRejectedRequestSource.description: The WWN that was the source of the RSCN, SCR, or SW_RSCN that was most recently rejected by this switch on this Fabric.

t11FcRscnRejectReasonCode.name: t11FcRscnRejectReasonCode
t11FcRscnRejectReasonCode.reference: ANSI INCITS 433-2007, Fibre Channel - Link Services (FC-LS), July 2007, Table 146. ANSI INCITS 418-2006, Fibre Channel - Switch Fabric - 4 (FC-SW-4), December 2006, Table 5.
t11FcRscnRejectReasonCode.description: This object contains the Reason Code of the most recent rejection by this switch of an RSCN, SCR or SW_RSCN on this Fabric.

t11FcRscnRejectReasonCodeExp.name: t11FcRscnRejectReasonCodeExp
t11FcRscnRejectReasonCodeExp.reference: ANSI INCITS 433-2007, Fibre Channel - Link Services (FC-LS), July 2007, Table 147. ANSI INCITS 418-2006, Fibre Channel - Switch Fabric - 4 (FC-SW-4), December 2006, Table 6.
t11FcRscnRejectReasonCodeExp.description: This object contains the Reason Code Explanation of the most recent rejection by this switch of an RSCN, SCR or SW_RSCN on this Fabric.

t11FcRscnRejectReasonVendorCode.name: t11FcRscnRejectReasonVendorCode
t11FcRscnRejectReasonVendorCode.reference: ANSI INCITS 433-2007, Fibre Channel - Link Services (FC-LS), July 2007, Table 148. ANSI INCITS 418-2006, Fibre Channel - Switch Fabric - 4 (FC-SW-4), December 2006, Section 6.1.3.
t11FcRscnRejectReasonVendorCode.description: This object contains the Reason Vendor Specific Code of the most recent rejection by this switch of an RSCN, SCR or SW_RSCN on this Fabric.

t11FcRscnElsRejectReqNotify.name: t11FcRscnElsRejectReqNotify
t11FcRscnElsRejectReqNotify.description: This notification is generated when a switch rejects an SCR or RSCN. The value of t11FcRscnRejectedRequestString indicates the binary content of the rejected request if available, or the zero-length string otherwise. The source of the rejected request is given by t11FcRscnRejectedRequestSource, and the reason for rejection is given by the values of t11FcRscnRejectReasonCode, t11FcRscnRejectReasonCodeExp and t11FcRscnRejectReasonVendorCode.

t11FcRscnIlsRejectReqNotify.name: t11FcRscnIlsRejectReqNotify
t11FcRscnIlsRejectReqNotify.description: This notification is generated when a switch rejects an SW_RSCN. The value of t11FcRscnRejectedRequestString indicates the binary content of the rejected request if available, or the zero-length string otherwise. The source of the rejected request is given by t11FcRscnRejectedRequestSource, and the reason for rejection is given by the values of t11FcRscnRejectReasonCode, t11FcRscnRejectReasonCodeExp and t11FcRscnRejectReasonVendorCode.

t11FcRscnCompliance.name: t11FcRscnCompliance
t11FcRscnCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities that implement this MIB.

t11FcRscnRegistrationGroup.name: t11FcRscnRegistrationGroup
t11FcRscnRegistrationGroup.description: A collection of objects for monitoring RSCN registrations.

t11FcRscnStatsGroup.name: t11FcRscnStatsGroup
t11FcRscnStatsGroup.description: A collection of objects for collecting RSCN-related statistics.

t11FcRscnNotifyControlGroup.name: t11FcRscnNotifyControlGroup
t11FcRscnNotifyControlGroup.description: A collection of notification control and notification information objects.

t11FcRscnNotifyGroup.name: t11FcRscnNotifyGroup
t11FcRscnNotifyGroup.description: A collection of notifications for monitoring ILS and ELS rejections by the RSCN module.
